result.name: The Coffee Academics Flagship

reviews.text: The food is alright. I had the acai bowl, which was surprisingly small of the size, but still tasty. The great coffee made up for the small portion of food. And an added bonus was that its free before 12pm if you order food! The staff was very friendly... would recommend for a good cup of coffee.

30 minutes to prepare a toast with avocado on it and got my wife order wrong. A nice place operated by a bunch of rabbits on chamomile. Food is good though just need to improve service. Avoid unless you have plenty of time. Like a year or so.

Nice atmosphere, Nice restaurant.. Foods are nice. The tea was very good too.
i recommend even it's a bit pricey.

Didn’t know this flagship has fancy dinner menu which actually taste pretty good. We had laksa pasta, steak and curly fries. Laksa pasta was delicious with generous serving of prawns. Coffee academics also provide space for monthly cats and dogs adoption events with Paws United at their different branches - such a caring organisation!
Amazing coffee brews... tasty bites.. nice hangout spot!
